    {
      "id": "a7783bfe_27eb5b7c",
      "file_path": "rest-services/dmaap-client/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/services/sdk/rest/services/dmaap/client/impl/MessageRouterPublisherImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 90,
      "message": "Using `replaceAll()` doesn't look nice, but I don't have any other ideas how to deal with quotes escaping which are the result of `JsonElement::toString`.\nI could use `JsonElement:: getAsString` instead, but then I would have to handle somehow situations, when one passes something that is not String.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3789,
        "name": "Izabela Zawadzka",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "izabela.zawadzka@nokia.com",
        "username": "izabelazawadzka"
      },
      "updated": "2019-05-28 10:17:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "8d9ccd05_8ecabaa5",
      "file_path": "rest-services/dmaap-client/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/services/sdk/rest/services/dmaap/client/impl/MessageRouterPublisherImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 83,
      "message": "What if content type is \"application/json; charset=utf-8\"? Maybe we shall move ContentType enum to the model and use it directly in our public API so we force clients to use predefined content types?\n\nDoes DMaaP MR support different content types? If the behavior is special only for Json then maybe we should define abstract class ContentType with subclass JsonContentType (singleton) and let's say OtherContentType(type: String). In Kotlin it would be easier:\n\nsealed class ContentType(val mime: String)\nobject JsonContentType : ContentType(\"application/json\")\nclass OtherContentType(mime: String): ContentType(mime)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2683,
        "name": "Piotr Jaszczyk",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "piotr.jaszczyk@nokia.com",
        "username": "jaszczur"
      },
      "updated": "2019-05-30 10:17:17.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
