    },
    {
      "id": "a133b280_6d6e2218",
      "file_path": "rest-services/dmaap-client/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/services/sdk/rest/services/dmaap/client/impl/MessageRouterPublisherImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 83,
      "message": "Filip suggested using ContentType enum in public API, but also said that maybe it would be better to make that change in new MR. \nBut, of course, I can do it here.\n\nAs far as I know (I was checking `readthedocks` and instructions), MR support exactly 2 content types: 'application/json' and 'text.plain'",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3789,
        "name": "Izabela Zawadzka",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "izabela.zawadzka@nokia.com",
        "username": "izabelazawadzka"
      },
      "updated": "2019-05-30 10:46:37.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "8d9ccd05_8ecabaa5",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "450bc116_5fda029d",
      "file_path": "rest-services/dmaap-client/src/main/java/org/onap/dcaegen2/services/sdk/rest/services/dmaap/client/impl/MessageRouterPublisherImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 94,
      "message": "If we want to send multiple messages with `text/plain`, content should look like\n\"message1\nmessage2\nmessage3\"\n\nMessageRouter figures out that we are sending multiple messages only if we split them with new line. So we should send one multi-line String (as far as I understand)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3789,
        "name": "Izabela Zawadzka",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "izabela.zawadzka@nokia.com",
        "username": "izabelazawadzka"
      },
      "updated": "2019-05-30 10:46:37.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "0eacd243_3e909e82",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "faed6164_85953c60",
